Privacy Policy for WebAppify

Effective Date: 7 June 2024

Welcome to WebAppify! Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your information when you use our mobile application and services.

1. Information We Collect
1.1 Personal Information
We may collect personal information from you when you interact with our mobile application and services. This information is provided voluntarily by you and may include:

Name: We collect your name to personalize your experience and to address you appropriately.

Email Address: Your email address is used for communication purposes, including account management, notifications, and updates regarding our services.

Business Name: If applicable, we may collect the name of your business to associate it with your account and to customize your app's branding.

Business Logo: You may provide your business logo to be displayed within your app to reflect your brand identity.

1.2 Usage Data
In addition to personal information, we also collect certain data automatically when you use our app. This may include:

Device Information: We collect information about the device you use to access our app, such as device type, operating system, and unique device identifiers. This helps us optimize our app for different devices and troubleshoot any compatibility issues.

Log Data: Our servers automatically record information that your device sends whenever you use our app. This may include your IP address, browser type, pages visited within the app, and timestamps. Log data is used for analytics purposes, such as analyzing app usage patterns, diagnosing technical issues, and ensuring the security of our services.

Usage Patterns: We track how you interact with our app, including the features you use, the duration of your sessions, and the actions you take. This data helps us understand how users engage with our app and enables us to make improvements to enhance the user experience.

2. How We Use Your Information
We use the information we collect to:

Provide, operate, and maintain our services
Customize and personalize your experience
Communicate with you, including sending promotional offers and notifications
Improve our services, including analyzing usage patterns and troubleshooting issues
Process transactions and manage accounts
Comply with legal obligations
3. How We Share Your Information
We do not share your personal information with third parties except in the following circumstances:

With your consent
With service providers who perform functions on our behalf (e.g., hosting services)
To comply with legal requirements (e.g., in response to a subpoena or court order)
To protect our rights, property, or safety, or the rights, property, or safety of others
4. Security of Your Information
We implement a variety of security measures to protect your personal information. However, no method of transmission over the Internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure. While we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.

5. Your Choices
You have several choices regarding your personal information:

You can update or delete your account information through the app settings.
You can unsubscribe from promotional emails by following the instructions in those emails.
You can disable push notifications through your device settings.
6. Children's Privacy
Our services are not directed to children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we become aware that we have inadvertently received personal information from a child under 13, we will delete such information from our records.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the effective date. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.

8. Contact Us
